  "steph-thrive-notes": "\ud83d\udca1 DANCER STRENGTH & PERFORMANCE PROGRAM\nSource: @frankiebiondi.physio | Saved Mar 4, 2026\n\nA 6-week small group strength program for competitive dancers, led by a registered physiotherapist (MScPT).\n\nDETAILS:\n\u2022 In-person, 8\u201310 dancers per group\n\u2022 Thursdays starting July 2, 2026\n\u2022 Location: Happiness is Dancing, Sudbury ON\n\u2022 $600/dancer (tax included) + 8-week home program\n\u2022 Age groups: 7 & under / 8\u20139 / 10\u201312 / 13+\n\u2022 Limited spots \u2014 first come first served\n\nWHY IT WORKS:\n\u2022 Physio-led = trust + premium positioning\n\u2022 Niche-specific (dancers only)\n\u2022 Multi-week commitment = recurring revenue\n\u2022 Age-tiered = wide audience from one program\n\nTHRIVE APPLICATION:\nCould do something similar \u2014 e.g. Pilates for Dancers, Postpartum Strength, or Teen Athlete Performance. Partner with a local physio or RMT. Small group (6\u201310), multi-week, seasonal intensive. Great way to fill the barn outside regular class schedule.\n",
  "steph-thrive-notes-v2": [
    {
      "id": "tn1772649600000",
      "title": "\ud83d\udca1 Dancer Strength & Performance Program",
